The paper focuses on incorporating external memory into generative models and using variational inference to guide memory lookups. This topic is closely related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, which suggests that cs.LG and cs.AI are likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper applies the proposed approach to the task of generative few-shot learning, which involves working with images and requires understanding of computer vision techniques, indicating that cs.CV is also a possible sub-category. The use of stochastic addressing and the emphasis on multimodality suggest that the paper may also be relevant to neural networks (cs.NE) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
